### APIM Debug Tracing Tests - Example showing comprehensive circuit breaker analysis
### 
### This test collection focuses specifically on APIM debug tracing functionality
### for analyzing circuit breaker behavior and policy execution flow.
###
### Prerequisites:
### 1. Run `azd up` to provision the infrastructure and create the VS Code settings file with all required variables
### 2. Ensure your APIM instance and backends are successfully deployed
###
### Service Principal Permissions (automatically configured):
### ✅ Uses the SAME App Registration created by the sample for JWT authentication
### ✅ The Terraform deployment automatically assigns the underlying Service Principal, the "Contributor" role for accessing the APIM service
### ✅ No manual role assignment required - everything is set up by `azd up`
### 
### Manual Service Principal Setup (only if needed for troubleshooting):
### If you need to manually verify or recreate the role assignment:
### 1. Search "App registrations" → Find app named "uai-gateway-[random]" or search by Application/Client ID
### 2. Copy the Application (Client) ID from the App Registration overview
### 3. Search "Enterprise applications" → Search by the Application (Client) ID from step 2  
### 4. This shows the Service Principal - copy its Object ID for role assignments
### 5. Azure CLI: az role assignment create --assignee <service-principal-object-id> --role "Contributor" --scope <apim-resource-id>
### 6. Azure Portal: APIM Service → Access control (IAM) → Add role assignment
###
### Test Coverage:
### - Azure Management API authentication for debug credentials
### - APIM debug token generation and usage  
### - Behavior and policy execution analysis with debug tracing
###
### Usage:
### 1. First run "Get Management API Token" request to authenticate
### 2. Run "Get Debug Credentials" request to obtain debug token
### 3. Execute debug-enabled requests to generate traces
### 4. Use "Retrieve APIM Trace" to analyze execution flow
###
### Learn More: https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/api-management/api-management-howto-api-inspector#enable-tracing-for-an-api

# Variables from VS Code REST Client settings
@apimEndpoint = {{apim_gateway_url}}/unified-ai
@apiVersion = 2025-01-01-preview
# APIM subscription key from VS Code settings
@apimSubKey = {{apim_subscription_key}}

###############################################################################
### Azure Management API Authentication
###############################################################################

### Get Management API Token for Azure Resource Management
# @name getManagementToken
# Gets token for Azure Management API endpoint
# This token is required for accessing APIM management operations like debug credentials
POST https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenant_id}}/oauth2/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials&client_id={{entra_app_id}}&client_secret={{entra_app_client_secret}}&resource=https%3A%2F%2Fmanagement.azure.com%2F

###

###############################################################################
### APIM Debug Credentials Management
###############################################################################

### Get Debug Credentials for APIM Gateway  
# @name listDebugCredentials
# Service Principal permissions are automatically configured by Terraform deployment
# Debug tokens have limited lifetime, refresh when needed
POST https://management.azure.com{{apim_resource_id}}/gateways/managed/listDebugCredentials?api-version=2024-05-01
Authorization: Bearer {{getManagementToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "apiId": "{{apim_resource_id}}/apis/gateway-wildcard",
    "purposes": ["tracing"]
}

### Extract debug token from response
@debugToken = {{listDebugCredentials.response.body.token}}

###

###############################################################################
### Debug Tracing Tests with APIM Debug Token
###############################################################################

### Test: OpenAI Chat Completion with Debug Tracing
# This test demonstrates APIM debug tracing functionality
# The Apim-Debug-Authorization header enables comprehensive tracing of the request flow
# 
# IMPORTANT: Look for the "Apim-Trace-Id" header in the response!
# This header contains the trace ID needed to retrieve detailed execution traces
# The trace ID is automatically captured below for use in trace retrieval
# 
# NOTE: First run "listDebugCredentials" above to get a fresh debug token!
# @name openaiDebugTest
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/gpt-4.1-mini/chat/completions?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Apim-Debug-Authorization: {{debugToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
      "content": "Test OpenAI API with debug tracing"
        }
    ],
  "max_tokens": 50
}

### Extract trace ID from OpenAI debug test response
@traceId = {{openaiDebugTest.response.headers.Apim-Trace-Id}}

###

###############################################################################
### APIM Trace Retrieval and Analysis
###############################################################################

### Retrieve APIM Trace (Automatically uses trace ID from OpenAI test)
# @name getTrace
# Retrieves the detailed trace information using the trace ID automatically captured from the OpenAI debug test
# This will show the complete policy execution flow, including all fragments and their execution order
POST https://management.azure.com{{apim_resource_id}}/gateways/managed/listTrace?api-version=2023-05-01-preview
Authorization: Bearer {{getManagementToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "traceId": "{{traceId}}"
}

###